## Playbook: Submit a Pull Request

When someone says "submit", "open a PR", "send my changes", or "contribute this":

1. **Verify gh CLI is authenticated:**
   ```bash
   gh auth status
   ```
   If not authenticated, help them run `gh auth login`.

2. **Ensure they have a fork:**
   ```bash
   gh repo fork hkjarral/Asterisk-AI-Voice-Agent --remote --remote-name fork
   ```
   (Idempotent — safe to run even if already forked.)

3. **Create a feature branch from develop:**
   ```bash
   git checkout develop
   git pull origin develop
   git checkout -b contrib/<short-description>
   ```

4. **Stage and commit all changes:**
   ```bash
   git add -A
   git commit -m "<descriptive message summarizing the change>"
   ```

5. **Push to their fork:**
   ```bash
   git push fork contrib/<short-description>
   ```

6. **Create the PR:**
   ```bash
   gh pr create \
     --repo hkjarral/Asterisk-AI-Voice-Agent \
     --base staging \
     --title "<short title>" \
     --body "## Summary
   <1-3 bullet points describing the change>

   ## Testing
   <how it was tested, or 'N/A for docs changes'>

   ---
   Submitted via AVA (AI-assisted contribution)"
   ```

7. **Share the PR URL** with the contributor. Tell them:
   "Your contribution has been submitted! A maintainer will review it. If they request changes, just tell me and I'll help you fix them."

8. **For follow-up changes** after review feedback:
   ```bash
   git add -A
   git commit -m "<fix description>"
   git push fork contrib/<short-description>
   ```
   The PR updates automatically.

